sub_title: Project Manager, International Capacity Building (VU Amsterdam)
summary: Mehek has been involved in several research studies, including for the Food and Agriculture Organisation of the United Nations (FAO), the Dutch Institute for Public Health and the Environment (RIVM) and for the VU University. During her Masters she has learned to solve complex public health issues in a structured manner using a multidisciplinary approach. Furthermore, she has experience in: critical analysis of literature; the preparation of research studies; data collection; analysis of both quantitative and qualitative data; and providing recommendations based on research findings. Working in international environments is her passion and her aim is to ensure that consumers are provided with safe and good quality food.
